compare publication metrics between journals","To identify all available published literature","To calculate statistical significance of results","To determine funding sources for research"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ECritical appraisal involves systematic evaluation of research methodology, potential sources of bias, statistical analysis, and clinical relevance. The primary purpose of this appraisal is to \u003Cstrong\u003Esystematically assess research quality and reliability\u003C/strong\u003E, enabling healthcare professionals to make informed decisions about whether research findings are valid and applicable to their clinical practice.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIdentifying all available published literature\u003C/strong\u003E describes systematic literature searching, which is a different skill from critical appraisal. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E While \u003Cstrong\u003Ecalculating statistical significance of results \u003C/strong\u003E is important, critical appraisal involves broader evaluation of study methodology, bias, and applicability. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDetermining funding sources for research\u003C/strong\u003E may be relevant to bias assessment, but is only one small aspect of critical appraisal. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EComparing publication metrics between journals \u003C/strong\u003Edoes not best describe the purpose of critical appraisal, as journal metrics do not necessarily reflect the quality or reliability of individual research articles.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Critical appraisal helps healthcare professionals evaluate the validity, reliability and applicability of research evidence.","Evidence-based practice requires systematic assessment of research quality to inform clinical decision-making.","Poor quality evidence can lead to incorrect conclusions and potentially harmful clinical decisions."],"references":["Al-Jundi A, Sakka S. Critical Appraisal of Clinical Research. J Clin Diagn Res. 2017 May;11(5):JE01-JE05. doi: 10.7860/JCDR/2017/26047.9942. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC5483707/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51635"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16660"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51635","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51635"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-29T14:32:44+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-28T23:39:52+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9351"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66187"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id